      "title": "Section 2",
      "content": "<p><em>Questions 15–27 refer to the texts below.</em></p><h2><span class='text-label'>Text 1</span> Hotel Front Desk Procedures</h2><p>The front desk team plays a crucial role in the success of our hotel. The following procedures ensure smooth operations and guest satisfaction:</p><p><strong>1. Check-in Process:</strong><br/>- Greet the guest with a friendly smile and offer assistance.<br/>- Verify the guest's reservation by asking for their identification and confirmation number.<br/>- Process the payment by accepting credit cards or cash, ensuring to provide a receipt.<br/>- Hand over the room keycard and inform the guest of the breakfast hours and Wi-Fi details.<br/>- Offer any additional services or inform about ongoing promotions.</p><p><strong>2. Handling Guest Complaints:</strong><br/>- Listen actively and empathize with the guest's concern without interrupting.<br/>- Apologize sincerely for any inconvenience caused.<br/>- Offer a solution such as upgrading their room, offering a discount, or alerting the appropriate department to address the issue.<br/>- Follow up with the guest to ensure satisfaction.</p><p><strong>3. Check-out Process:</strong><br/>- Confirm the guest's departure date and prepare their bill in advance.<br/>- Verify charges for room service, mini-bar use, and any other expenses.<br/>- Thank the guest for their stay and inquire about feedback.<br/>- Offer assistance with luggage or transportation as needed.</p><hr/><h2><span class='text-label'>Text 2</span> Housekeeping Safety Procedures</h2><p>Ensuring the safety of our housekeeping staff is a top priority. Follow these safety procedures to minimize risks:</p><p><strong>1. Personal Protective Equipment (PPE):</strong><br/>- Wear gloves when using cleaning chemicals to prevent skin irritation.<br/>- Use masks when working in dust-prone areas or when using sprays.<br/>- Ensure non-slip shoes are worn at all times to prevent falls.</p><p><strong>2. Handling Chemicals:</strong><br/>- Read labels carefully and follow manufacturer's instructions for all cleaning products.<br/>- Store chemicals in a locked cabinet after each use and ensure it is well-ventilated.<br/>- Never mix different chemicals; this can produce harmful gases.</p><p><strong>3. Equipment Safety:</strong><br/>- Inspect vacuum cleaners and other equipment for damage before use.<br/>- Ensure cords do not lay across walkways to prevent tripping.<br/>- Report any faulty equipment to the maintenance department immediately.</p><p><strong>4. Lifting and Carrying:</strong><br/>- Use proper body mechanics when lifting heavy objects; bend at the knees, not the waist.<br/>- Ask for assistance if an object is too heavy to lift alone.<br/>- Use a cart for transporting multiple items across rooms.</p><p><strong>5. Emergency Procedures:</strong><br/>- Familiarize yourself with the nearest emergency exits in each area.<br/>- Participate in all scheduled safety drills and briefings.<br/>- Report any accidents or injuries to your supervisor immediately, regardless of severity.</p>",
